### Module 2 — Express Fundamentals
### Install the VS Code "REST Client" extension to run these in-editor
### Or copy the curl equivalents into your terminal

@base = http://localhost:3000

# ─── SPRINT ──────────────────────────────────────────────

### Hello world
GET {{base}}/hello

###
# curl http://localhost:3000/hello


# ─── DEEP DIVE: req object ───────────────────────────────

### Route params + query string
GET {{base}}/echo/james?color=blue&size=large

###
# curl "http://localhost:3000/echo/james?color=blue&size=large"


### POST with a JSON body — notice how body appears in response
POST {{base}}/echo
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "James",
  "job": "developer"
}

###
# curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/echo \
#   -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#   -d '{"name":"James","job":"developer"}'


### Custom headers — add your own and see them reflected
GET {{base}}/echo/test
X-My-Header: hello-world
Authorization: Bearer fake-token-for-learning

###
# curl http://localhost:3000/echo/test \
#   -H "X-My-Header: hello-world" \
#   -H "Authorization: Bearer fake-token-for-learning"


# ─── DEEP DIVE: Controlling responses ────────────────────

### Different status codes
GET {{base}}/status-demo?code=201
###
GET {{base}}/status-demo?code=400
###
GET {{base}}/status-demo?code=404

###
# curl -v "http://localhost:3000/status-demo?code=404"


### HTML response — observe the Content-Type header
GET {{base}}/html-demo

###
# curl -v http://localhost:3000/html-demo


### Plain text response
GET {{base}}/text-demo

###
# curl -v http://localhost:3000/text-demo


### Custom response headers — use -v to see them
GET {{base}}/headers-demo

###
# curl -v http://localhost:3000/headers-demo
